01:50:18.745 --> 01:50:23.079
you could've looked those pricks
in the eye and told them the truth.

01:50:23.149 --> 01:50:25.640
Under oath. Told them
they were full of shit.

01:50:25.719 --> 01:50:30.053
And barring that,
you could've at least told me.

01:50:30.123 --> 01:50:35.060
But see, it really wasn't any of your
business either, and it still isn't.

01:50:35.128 --> 01:50:38.620
There's something about
almost puking on a Havana...

01:50:38.698 --> 01:50:41.064
that just turns a girl...
to blush.

01:50:41.134 --> 01:50:45.468
This letter from Jack Bennet <i>... </i>

01:50:45.538 --> 01:50:50.771
and Larry Bellows, affidavit, I guess,
that you got from Webster.

01:50:50.844 --> 01:50:54.007
It pretty much says
that nothing happened that night.

01:50:54.080 --> 01:50:58.244
- They're ready
to come forward to be deposed.
- That's very good of them.

01:50:58.318 --> 01:51:01.879
So, that's it. The end.
Good guys win.

01:51:01.955 --> 01:51:05.254
I'm gonna call a press conference
tomorrow, read that letter...

01:51:05.325 --> 01:51:09.989
and damn it if you don't have
the fastest confirmation on record.

01:51:10.063 --> 01:51:11.997
No, sir.

01:51:12.065 --> 01:51:14.659
"No, sir"?
What, "No, sir"?

01:51:14.734 --> 01:51:19.433
I would prefer that we not
have the press conference, sir.

01:51:19.506 --> 01:51:22.873
Laine, maybe you've been out
of law school too long.

01:51:22.942 --> 01:51:26.105
- This is what they call
exculpatory evidence.
- Yes, I realize that.

01:51:26.179 --> 01:51:30.081
- This is your ticket to wherever
history is gonna take you.
- Yes.

01:51:30.150 --> 01:51:33.881
But principles only mean
something if you stick by them
when they're inconvenient.

01:51:35.522 --> 01:51:38.389
If I ever did
answer the questions...

01:51:38.458 --> 01:51:42.155
you know,
even to exonerate myself...

01:51:42.228 --> 01:51:45.857
that would mean that it was
okay for them to have been
asked in the first place...

01:51:45.932 --> 01:51:47.866
and it isn't.

01:51:47.934 --> 01:51:50.664
- You would sacrifice your reputation?
- Yes, I would.

01:51:50.737 --> 01:51:54.264
People have sacrificed
a lot more for a lot less.

01:51:54.340 --> 01:51:56.331
<i>[People Chattering]</i>

01:51:56.409 --> 01:52:00.641
- We've got him! We have Goliath.
- Sir, are you all right, sir?

01:52:00.714 --> 01:52:04.172
- It's okay, guys. Busted.
- POTUS is secure.

01:52:04.517 --> 01:52:07.816
<i>[Radio Announcer]</i>
<i>Of course, the president addressing</i>
<i>a joint session of Congress... </i>

01:52:07.887 --> 01:52:10.321
<i>is always unusual, </i>
<i>always an event. </i>

01:52:10.390 --> 01:52:13.291
<i>This speech is scheduled</i>
<i>to begin momentarily. </i>

01:52:13.359 --> 01:52:16.760
<i>We understand the president</i>
<i>has arrived at the U.S. Capitol. </i>

01:52:16.830 --> 01:52:20.322
[Laine] I don't care if I never
see any of these guys again.

01:52:20.400 --> 01:52:24.837
<i>[Radio] Sources in the White House</i>
<i>have told us that the president... </i>

01:52:24.904 --> 01:52:28.533
- It's gonna be okay.
<i>- Does intend to withdraw the name</i>
<i>of Senator Laine B. Hanson... </i>

01:52:28.608 --> 01:52:33.511
I still have a year and a half on
my term. That's a long time to recover.

01:52:33.580 --> 01:52:39.041
- Then there's always...
<i>- Given the stunning charges</i>
<i>made against Governor Hathaway... </i>

01:52:39.119 --> 01:52:43.283
- Laine, honey, it's gonna be fine.
<i>- Those on the inside are suggesting... </i>

01:52:43.356 --> 01:52:45.324
- It's gonna be okay.
<i>- The president will designate... </i>

01:52:45.391 --> 01:52:48.656
<i>-Ambassador Francis J. Malloy</i>
<i>as his number two. </i>
- Yeah, thanks.

01:52:50.063 --> 01:52:52.293
Pace me at five to ten, okay?

01:52:55.535 --> 01:53:00.370
<i>[Radio Announcer]</i>
<i>... after the greeting</i>
<i>of the president of the United States. </i>

01:53:00.440 --> 01:53:04.274
<i>Mr. Speaker, the president</i>
<i>of the United States of America. </i>

01:54:19.686 --> 01:54:22.154
<i>Thank you. </i>

01:54:24.557 --> 01:54:29.893
Napoleon once said,
when asked to explain the lack
of great statesmen in the world...

01:54:29.963 --> 01:54:32.454
that, "to get power...

01:54:32.532 --> 01:54:36.024
you need to display
absolute pettiness.

01:54:36.102 --> 01:54:40.198
To exercise power,
you need to show true greatness."

01:54:40.273 --> 01:54:44.835
<i>Such pettiness and such greatness</i>
<i>are rarely found in one person. </i>

01:54:44.911 --> 01:54:48.347
<i>I look upon the events</i>
<i>of the past weeks... </i>

01:54:48.414 --> 01:54:52.214
<i>and I've never come so to grips</i>
<i>with that quotation. </i>

01:54:52.285 --> 01:54:54.617
So, ladies and gentlemen
of this Congress...

01:54:54.687 --> 01:55:00.091
it pains my soul to tell you
that you have brought blood
and shame under this great dome.

01:55:00.159 --> 01:55:04.619
Your leadership has raised
the stakes of hate to a level...

01:55:04.697 --> 01:55:09.259
where we can no longer separate
the demagogue from the truly inspired.

01:55:09.335 --> 01:55:14.671
And believe this,
there are traitors among us.

01:55:14.741 --> 01:55:19.337
<i>And I'm not talking about those of you</i>
<i>who sided against your party leadership. </i>

01:55:19.412 --> 01:55:23.371
<i>I'm talking about those of you</i>
<i>who were patriots to your party... </i>

01:55:23.449 --> 01:55:27.078
but traitors
to the necessary end result:

01:55:27.153 --> 01:55:30.384
<i>that of righteousness, </i>
<i>the truth... </i>

01:55:30.456 --> 01:55:35.792
the concept of making
the American dream blind to gender.

01:55:35.862 --> 01:55:40.265
<i>And you know, </i>
<i>I am not free of blame. </i>

01:55:40.333 --> 01:55:42.733
Right from the start
I should've come down here...

01:55:42.802 --> 01:55:46.033
pointed a finger your way...

01:55:46.105 --> 01:55:48.198
pointed a finger <i>your</i> way...

01:55:48.274 --> 01:55:51.801
<i>and asked you, </i>
<i>"Have you no decency, sir?"</i>

01:55:53.646 --> 01:55:56.740
<i>Yesterday... </i>

01:55:56.816 --> 01:55:59.148
I met...

01:55:59.218 --> 01:56:02.016
<i>Mr. Runyon... </i>

01:56:02.088 --> 01:56:05.182
you may walk out on me,
you may walk out on this body...

01:56:05.258 --> 01:56:10.093
but you cannot walk out
on the will of the American people.

01:56:10.163 --> 01:56:13.155
<i>Americans are a good people, </i>
<i>they're a just people, Mr. Runyon... </i>

01:56:13.232 --> 01:56:16.998
and they will forgive you,
but they will not forget.

01:56:17.070 --> 01:56:19.698
Hate and ego
have no place residing...

01:56:19.772 --> 01:56:24.436
in what my good friend Laine Hanson
calls the chapel of democracy.

01:56:24.510 --> 01:56:26.410
<i>So, let me make one thing clear. </i>

01:56:26.479 --> 01:56:31.007
<i>You come at us with whatever weapons</i>
<i>that you have in your arsenal... </i>

01:56:31.084 --> 01:56:33.848
but there is
no weapon as powerful...

01:56:33.920 --> 01:56:37.481
as that of an idea
whose time has come.

01:56:37.557 --> 01:56:41.653
A woman will serve in the highest level
of the Executive. Simple as that.

01:56:41.728 --> 01:56:45.027
<i>Yesterday... </i>

01:56:45.098 --> 01:56:48.659
I spoke with Laine Hanson.

01:56:48.735 --> 01:56:52.068
I told her that she could decide
her own destiny.

01:56:52.138 --> 01:56:55.107
If she wanted to continue
her fight for confirmation...

01:56:55.174 --> 01:56:58.871
that I would stand beside her.

01:56:58.945 --> 01:57:01.812
She has asked me
to allow her to step aside.

01:57:01.881 --> 01:57:06.545
<i>She told me that she wanted</i>
<i>my administration to end on a note... </i>

01:57:06.619 --> 01:57:10.316
of triumph
and not controversy.

01:57:10.390 --> 01:57:15.919
Understand, those of you who worked
to bring Laine Hanson down...

01:57:15.995 --> 01:57:19.624
that she asked to have her name
withdrawn from consideration...

01:57:19.699 --> 01:57:23.567
not because she isn't great,
but because she isn't petty.

01:57:23.636 --> 01:57:27.231
<i>Because those two</i>
<i>conflicting leadership traits... </i>

01:57:27.306 --> 01:57:31.037
<i>could not live as one</i>
<i>within her body or her soul. </i>

01:57:31.110 --> 01:57:34.568
Greatness.
It comes in many forms.

01:57:34.647 --> 01:57:38.549
Sometimes it comes in the form
of sacrifice. That's the loneliest form.

01:57:38.618 --> 01:57:43.021
<i>Now, it turns out</i>
<i>that Laine Hanson is a woman... </i>

01:57:43.089 --> 01:57:46.581
an American
of devout principle...

01:57:46.659 --> 01:57:49.685
<i>and she has inspired me</i>
<i>to act alike... </i>

01:57:49.762 --> 01:57:54.995
and I cannot accept
Senator Hanson's withdrawal.

01:57:55.068 --> 01:58:00.335
<i>And I'm now calling for an immediate</i>
<i>vote of confirmation of Laine Hanson. </i>

01:58:00.406 --> 01:58:02.374
And, Mr. Speaker...

01:58:02.442 --> 01:58:06.936
I would like to make this
a live roll call.

01:58:07.013 --> 01:58:09.811
I want to see the faces
of those of you...

01:58:09.882 --> 01:58:13.045
who would eliminate the possibility
of greatness in American leadership...

01:58:13.119 --> 01:58:17.351
because of half-truths,
lies and innuendoes.

01:58:17.423 --> 01:58:20.449
I will not be deterred
by partisanship.

01:58:20.526 --> 01:58:22.460
I will not be deterred
by misogyny.

01:58:22.528 --> 01:58:25.019
<i>I will not be deterred</i>
<i>by hate. </i>

01:58:25.098 --> 01:58:28.261
You have now come face-to-face
with my will.

01:58:29.335 --> 01:58:32.600
<i>Confirm my nominee, </i>
<i>heal this nation... </i>

01:58:32.672 --> 01:58:36.802
and let the American people
explode into this new millennium...

01:58:36.876 --> 01:58:42.075
with the exhilaration of being true
to the glory of this democracy.

01:58:42.148 --> 01:58:43.911
Thank you.

01:59:29.862 --> 01:59:32.854
How's that for a swan song?

01:59:32.932 --> 01:59:35.332
You're back, Laine.

01:59:35.401 --> 01:59:38.427
Yeah, I know.

